<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">even gemma3:12b gets it correct:<p>~&gt; ollama run gemma3:12b-it-qat
&gt;&gt;&gt;     ffmpeg command to convert movie.mov into a reasonably sized mp4<p>Here&#x27;s a good ffmpeg command to convert `movie.mov` to a reasonably sized MP4, along with explanations to help you adjust it:<p>```bash
ffmpeg -i movie.mov -c:v libx264 -crf 23 -preset medium -c:a aac -b:a 128k movie.mp4
```<p>*Explanation of the command and the options:*</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44371287&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44367638%2344371287" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
